**Step 1 :**
<text>Download and install apps

</text>
    <link page="download"  name="Download Page" >
<text>

Install Apps in order 
    RNX Core >> RNX Neo >> RNX XIO
    
</text>

**Step 2 :**
<text>Installing Linux

	run below command in RNX Terminal

</text>
```bash
rnx get-default-linux
```
<text>
	then set your linux in prompt
	1) select debian
	2) set root password
	3) user setup
	
	This will install and setup debian on android

</text>
**Step 3:**

<text>to Start basic services 

	run below commands as root user
        run command "su" to switch to root user
        then enter your password

</text>
```bash
rnx_uwax enable xio
```
<text>
xio is GUI Display for RNX


to disable startup service 
run command 

</text>
```bash
rnx_uwax disable xio
```

